Excellent review from Bangladesh, credit to the bowler as he was quite confident that he had got rid of Erwee and convinced his skipper as well. Ebadot Hossain finally gets his reward and he has been just brilliant in this morning session. This is a length ball, jagging back in late from outside off. Erwee prods and looks to play it across the line. He misses and gets pinged on his back pad. The Ball Tracker suggests that Erwee is plumb in front and the on-field decision is overturned.
Howout: lbw b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Back of a length, around off and jagging back in sharply. Keegan Petersen stays back to defend but he gets an inside edge onto his pad.
On a length, around off. Keegan Petersen blocks it out.
FOUR! Top shot! A full ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen leans and drives it through the cover region for a boundary. He is off the mark in style!

DROPPED! Tossed up, well outside off. Dean Elgar reaches out and looks to drive it away from his body. It takes the outside edge and goes quickly towards Najmul Hossain Shanto, to his left, at first slip who spills it. A tough one but you expect that to be taken at this level.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Dean Elgar gets on top of the bounce and carves it through the cover region for a boundary.
Darted on the pads. Elgar works it around the corner for a run.
Around off. Blocked out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Keegan Petersen rocks back and cuts it to the cover fielder who half-stops it. A single taken!
A quicker ball, on a length, around middle. Dean Elgar stays back and nudges it behind square on the leg side for a couple of runs.
Back of a length, just outside off. Keegan Petersen blocks it off the back foot.
On a length, around middle and leg. Keegan Petersen tucks it around the corner and rotates the strike.
Nice and full, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone.
Good-length ball, angling in from outside off. Dean Elgar covers his off pole and lets it be.
This is a length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms to it.
Short of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar stays back and works it behind square on the off side for a couple of runs.
Floated, full and outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone.
Another ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen has no shot to offer.
Looped up, on a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen prods and leaves it alone yet again.
Flatter and a bit quicker, around middle. Keegan Petersen rocks back and pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off. Left alone.
A bit quicker, around off. Keegan Petersen hangs back and dabs it onto the deck. The skipper starts with a maiden over!
A length ball, nipping back in just that little bit from off. Dean Elgar blocks it off the back foot.

DROPPED! Oh, dear! Bangladesh have been really sloppy in the field this morning. Elgar gets a life! Back of a length, around the corridor of uncertainty. Elgar hangs hit bat around. It takes the thick outside edge towards Yasir Ali at second slip who puts it down. The ball goes past him and the batters take two runs. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but Elgar had made it home.
Good-length ball, outside off. Dean Elgar taps it to the off side and rotates the strike.
A length ball, way outside off. Keegan Petersen lets it be.
FOUR! CRUNCHED! Short and wide, outside off. Keegan Petersen stands tall and cuts it uppishly past Mushfiqur Rahim at backward point for a boundary.
On a length, around off. Keegan Petersen defends it to the off side and collects a run.
Good-length ball, angling in from middle. Keegan Petersen stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
On a length, around off. Keegan Petersen blocks it off the front foot.
A full ball, on middle. Keegan Petersen prods and pushes it to mid on. The batters cross ends.
Short of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it through cover and collects a run. Elgar moves to 47!
Full and around middle. Keegan Petersen flicks it behind square on the leg side for a single.

FOUR! FIFTY FOR ELGAR! This was a bit uppish but well past the diving gully fielder. Back of a length, outside off. Elgar stays back and looks to push it through the off side. It goes off the outer half of the blade, past the gully fielder and races away to the fence. He raises his bat to the dressing room to take all the applause.

A very loud shout for LBW but the umpire says no! This is a loopy ball, outside off and spinning in late. Keegan Petersen prods and looks to play it across the line. He misses and gets hit on his pad. The impact might have been outside off and hence, Bangladesh do not opt for a review.
Floated, around middle. Keegan Petersen works it to square leg for a single.
FOUR! Excellent timing on that one! An overpitched ball, around leg. Elgar prods and flicks it through the vacant square leg region for a boundary.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Dean Elgar rocks back and cuts it to the cover fielder.
Nicely tossed up, outside off. Dean Elgar drives it to the mid off fielder.
A bit short and outside off. Dean Elgar rocks back and pushes it to cover. Not in the gap though!
Back of a length, angling down the leg side. Keegan Petersen tries to flick it away but misses.
Ahmed bangs in a short delivery, outside off. Keegan Petersen dabs it to point.

What a beautiful delivery. A length ball, outside off. It nips in off the deck. Keegan Petersen tries to defend it out but fails to do so on the front foot. Keegan Petersen gets hit on his thigh pad, in front of the stumps. Khaled Ahmed appeals but the umpire is unmoved and so is his skipper, Mominul Haque. Oh dear, the replays later show that the ball would have hit the stumps. Bangladesh camp is not happy. The umpires have not been on cue this morning.
Length ball, on off, blocked out.
On a length, defended out.
Length, on the pads. Keegan Petersen flicks it through mid-wicket for a single.
FOUR BYES! Misses everyone! It is looped up, around leg and turns away sharply. It goes past the keeper down to fine leg for a boundary. The umpire signals byes.

FOUR BYES! More extra runs. It is full and on leg. Keegan Petersen set himself up for the reverse-sweep but misses it completely. The ball goes past Mushfiqur Rahim at leg slip. It races away to the fine leg fence.
On leg, defended to short mid on.
Full, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen comes down the track, eases it to long on for a single.
Angled in on off. Dean Elgar blocks it on his front foot.
Fuller, on middle. Dean Elgar pats it back to the bowler.
A length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen punches it through covers for a brace.
Full length, on the stumps. Keegan Petersen shuffles across and blocks it to mid-wicket off the inner half.
Fuller, on the pads. Keegan Petersen tries to flick it away to the leg side. The ball goes to cover off the leading edge. The batters cross for a single.

Swing and a miss! Good length, outside off, it flies off the deck. Dean Elgar stays back, tries to play away from his body. He gets beaten on the outside edge. Dean Elgar kicks the ground in frustration.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar shuffles across and shoulders his arms.
This one carries as well! A length ball, outside off. This one climbs off the deck. Dean Elgar shoulders his arms at it.
Loopy ball, around off, it turns down leg. Keegan Petersen flicks it to square leg with the turn for a single.
On off, Elgar eases it to mid on.
Tossed up, around off. Dean Elgar pushes it to cover for one.
Full, on the stumps. Keegan Petersen prods and defends it to the leg side.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen clips it past short leg.

This is full and angled down leg. Keegan Petersen stays inside the crease. He tries to flick it away but misses. It might've brushed his pads. The fielders around the batter appeal for lbw, soon Hasan joins in with a stifled appeal. The umpire is unmoved. No review taken.
Back of a length, outside off. Dean Elgar cuts it to deep square leg for a single.
Length ball, on top of off. Keegan Petersen gets behind the line and blocks it out watchfully.
Full, on off. Keegan Petersen pushes it gently towards mid off.
Back of a length, on the fourth stump line. Keegan Petersen pushes it to mid off.
Full length, on fifth stump. Keegan Petersen defends it to cover.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Keegan Petersen stays back, gets his blade down in time to block it out. Just a single of the over. Khaled Ahmed continues his good work with the ball.
Fuller, on the pads. Dean Elgar clips it to square leg for a single. 100 is up for South Africa.
Flighted, full and outside off. It grips and turns in off the deck. Keegan Petersen shuffles across the stumps and takes a blow on his pads, outside the line though.
On off, defended out.
Tossed up, around off. Keegan Petersen blocks it to cover.
Fuller, on off. It turns in off the deck. Keegan Petersen fails to flick it away. He gets pinged on his pads. Hasan appeals but the umpire shows no interest.
On off, blocked out watchfully.
Full length, outside off. Dean Elgar leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it to cover for a quick single.
Ahmed bowls a length ball, angled into the pads. Keegan Petersen hangs back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full length, wide of off. Keegan Petersen steps forward and pushes it back to the bowler off the toe-end of the blade.
Full length, on the off stump. Keegan Petersen drives it to mid on.
Length ball, on off, blocked out watchfully.
Fuller, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it to cover for an easy single.
Full toss, on off. Keegan Petersen comes down the track and hits it to the right of the bowler. Hasan dives to that side and makes a half-stop. The ball rolls to the man at mid on.
A single now as this is worked towards mid on.
Full, outside off. Dean Elgar pushes it out with his pad.
Tossed up, outside off. Dean Elgar drives it to cover.
Short ball, outside off. Dean Elgar cuts it through cover for a brace. THAT WILL BE LUNCH AT DAY 4.
Back of a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen lets it be.
FOUR! Keegan Petersen bags the first boundary post-Lunch session. Shorter in length, outside off. Keegan Petersen cuts it through covers for four.
A length ball, on off. Keegan Petersen defends it out solidly.
Outside off. Keegan Petersen leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, just outside off. Keegan Petersen blocks it out watchfully.
It is length ball, outside off. Keegan Petersen shoulders his arms at it.
Short, on off. Dean Elgar blocks it out.
Around off, pushed to cover.
Elgar flicks a full delivery to mid-wicket for one.
Two runs now! Tossed up, around off. Keegan Petersen comes down the track and flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
On off, Keegan Petersen blocks it out watchfully.
A single to end the over! Full, on the pads. Keegan Petersen clips it to mid-wicket for a single.
On a length, outside off. Keegan Petersen taps it past the backward point fielder and takes a run.
Short of a length, around off. Dean Elgar blocks it off the back foot.
A full ball, outside off. Dean Elgar mistimes his drive towards cover and scampers through to the other end.
A bit of inswing for Taskin! A length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Keegan Petersen looks to drive but it goes off the outer half towards deep cover for a run.
Good-length delivery, around off. Elgar gets behind the line of the ball and tucks it to mid-wicket.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Dean Elgar leans and pushes it to cover.
An appeal for LBW but the umpire says no! Tossed up, outside off. Keegan Petersen kneels and looks to reverse-sweep but he misses and gets hit on his pad. The impact might have been outside off.
Full and on off. Keegan Petersen pushes it back to the bowler.
Flatter ball, turning in from middle. Keegan Petersen rocks back and tucks it to square leg.
Another ball, flatter and quicker, on a length, and spinning in from middle. Keegan Petersen works it towards mid-wicket.
Keegan Petersen skips down the track and drives it to mid on.
Floated, full and on off. Keegan Petersen comes down the track and drills it back to the bowler.
Play and a miss! Back of a length, well outside off. Elgar hangs back and throws his bat at it. The ball zips past his blade.
On a length and nipping back in from off. Dean Elgar prods and works it to mid on.

A loud shout for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! Bangladesh though have sent it upstairs. Was there any bat involved in it? No, says the UltraEdge! The Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball would have crashed into the middle stump. It is three reds. Lovely delivery from Taskin! This was a length ball, nipping back in just that little bit from off. Elgar sits back and tries to keep it out. He misses as the ball beats the inside edge of his bat. Elgar is pinged on the pads and Taskin Ahmed appeals. Bangladesh opt for a review as the on-field umpire doesn't agree. Three reds on the Ball Tracker and it is pumb in front. The on-field decision is overturned! Massive wicket for Bangladesh!
Howout: lbw b Taskin Ahmed

Commentary: Around off. Temba Bavuma blocks it out.
Pitches it up, outside off. Bavuma drives but Mehidy Hasan at extra cover dives to his left and stops it.
Short of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma cuts it nicely but fails to find the gap. He hits it straight to the backward point fielder. A wicket-maiden from Taskin Ahmed!
Floated, outside off. Keegan Petersen skips down the track and keeps it out.
This is darted on the pads. Keegan Petersen tucks it around the corner and settles for a single.
Tosses it up, outside off. Bavuma prods but keeps his bat away from the line of the ball.
Flatter and around middle. Temba Bavuma defends it to the leg side.
Edged but safe! Flatter and quicker, going on with the angle from just outside off. Temba Bavuma sits back to block but it goes off the thick outside edge, past the slip fielder for a brace.
Slightly shorter in length, outside off. Temba Bavuma mistimes his cut shot towards the mid off fielder.
On a length, around middle. Keegan Petersen defends it towards mid-wicket.

A big mix-up but no harm done! Although, had that been another direct hit from Mehidy Hasan, it was curtains for Keegan Petersen! A length ball, around off. KP taps it to cover and looks for a run. Temba Bavuma sends him back. Mehidy Hasan misses his shy at the striker's end and KP survives.
On a length, around off. Kept out.
Back of a length, just outside off. Keegan Petersen defends it to the off side and takes a run.

Edged but it falls short of the fielder! A length ball, just outside off. Bavuma looks to block it off the front foot. It takes the outside edge and goes towards the slip fielder, on the bounce. It didn't carry to the fielder there as Bavuma played it with soft hands.
Pitched up, around off. Temba Bavuma keeps it out.
FOUR! Nicely played. It is tossed up, full and outside off. Keegan Petersen stride forward and drives it through covers for an exceptional boundary.
Fuller, on off. Keegan Petersen pushes it to the right of the bowler.
On off, clipped to mid on.
Flatter, on leg. Keegan Petersen blocks it to short leg.
Quicker and fuller, on the pads. Keegan Petersen flicks it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full and on off. Keegan Petersen comes down the track and pats it back to the bowler. The lead is 193 now.
Length ball, outside off. Temba Bavuma lets it be.
Landing on a length, on top of off. Temba Bavuma defends it out watchfully.
Fuller, on off. Temba Bavuma blocks it to the leg side.
Good length, in the corridor of uncertainty. Temba Bavuma leaves it alone for the keeper.
Full length, outside off. Bavuma drives it to cover.
Length ball, on the pads. Temba Bavuma flicks it to mid-wicket for a quick single. He will retain the strike.
Floated and full, on off. Bavuma tucks it to short leg.
Full, on off. Bavuma defends it to short leg yet again.
Touch fuller, on leg. Bavuma eases it down to long on for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Elation for Bangladesh. They pick up the third wicket of the innings. Mehidy Hasan gets his first wicket of the innings. He gets rid of a set batter in Keegan Petersen. It is fuller, quicker and on the pads. Keegan Petersen clips it straight to short leg. Mahmudul Hasan Joy stationed there, stays low and grabs the ball sharply. Keegan Petersen trudges back off the field.
Howout: c Mahmudul Hasan Joy b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Full, on the off stump. Ryan Rickelton prods and blocks it into the deck.
Full, on leg. Ryan Rickelton clips it to short fine leg.
Back of a length, outside off. Temba Bavuma defends it to the off side.
Full length, on the stumps. Bavuma defends it back to the bowler.
On a length, outside off, nips in a touch late. Temba Bavuma steps across and shoulders his arms at it.

OUT! CAUGHT! OH MY GOD! Yasir Ali, you beauty! In the morning session, Ali did drop a catch at slips. But this chance is even tougher and he grabs it with a single hand. Temba Bavuma cannot do anything about it other than walking back to the dressing room. Coming to the delivery - it is a length ball, around off, shaping away off the deck. Temba Bavuma hangs his blade away from his body. The ball takes the outside edge, goes to the left of first slip. Yasir Ali dives to that side and takes a stunning one-handed catch. Bangladesh are back in the game now.
Howout: c Yasir Ali b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Full length, just outside off. Kyle Verreynne blocks it to cover.
FOUR! Kyle Verreynne gets off the mark with a boundary. A length ball, angled down leg. Kyle Verreynne tickles it down to fine leg for a boundary. The lead moves to 199.
Fuller, outside off. Ryan Rickelton prods and tries to defend it to silly point. But it lands short of the fielder there.
This is full, on middle. Ryan Rickelton flicks it to short leg.
Full, outside off. Ryan Rickelton drives it to mid off. The fielder there misfields and the batters take a single. South Africa now lead by 200 runs!
Flighted, full and on leg. Kyle Verreynne fails to defend it out. The ball lobs to short leg off the pads.
On off, clipped to mid on.
Fuller, around off. Kyle Verreynne tries to defend it on the front foot. He gets an inside edge onto the pads.
A full ball, angling in from outside off. Ryan Rickelton leaves it alone.
Good-length delivery, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton dabs it onto the deck.
Another ball, back of a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton defends it to the off side.
A bumper, angling down leg. Ryan Rickelton ducks underneath. The umpire calls it wide for height.
On a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it with ease.
Back of a length, outside off. Ryan pushes it to the off side.
Full and outside off. Ryan Rickelton drives it to the fielder at mid off.
A full ball, around off. Kyle digs it out to the off side for a single.
Flatter and around off. Ryan Rickelton rocks back and punches it to cover.
Tossed up, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
This is a flatter ball, on middle. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and flicks it to mid-wicket.
A quicker ball, on a length and going on with the angle. Ryan manages to defend it off the back foot.
This is darted on the pads. Ryan Rickelton tucks it around the corner for a run.
Short of a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
A short ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton pulls it along the ground, in front of square on the leg side for a brace.
Hossain bowls it full, around off. Ryan defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! SMASHED! Short and wide, outside off. Ryan stays back, throws his bat it. It goes off the outer half of the bat and over the slip cordon for a boundary.
Back of a length, around middle. Ryan Rickelton tucks it to square leg, off the back foot.
A full ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton prods and pushes it to mid on. 6 runs off the over!
Floated, full and on middle. Kyle Verreynne wrists it to mid-wicket.
Nicely tossed up, on middle. Kyle Verreynne blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, turning in from middle. Kyle Verreynne rocks back and tickles it to short fine leg.
This is a flatter ball, turning in sharply from outside off. Kyle Verreynne gets cramped for room as he looks to cut that one.
Another ball, quicker and on middle. Kyle Verreynne manages to dab it onto the deck.
This one spins in sharply from outside off. Kyle Verreynne sits back in his crease and defends it out watchfully. Another maiden over from Mehidy Hasan!
Ahmed goes 'round the wicket and serves a good-length ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
Ahmed drags his length back a bit, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton stands tall and punches it to mid off.
FOUR! Nicely played! Short of a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and caresses it through the point region to bag a boundary.
BEATEN! This is a length ball, outside off and staying a tad low. Ryan looks to push it through the off side, off the back foot but the ball sneaks past his blade.
Short of a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton punches it past the fielder at cover and rotates the strike.
Good-length ball, outside off. Kyle Verreynne stays back and pushes it towards cover, off the back foot.
Fuller, on off. Ryan Rickelton defends it out solidly.
Around off, Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.
Fuller, outside off. Ryan Rickelton pushes it to mid off for a single.

It is a loopy ball, around off. Kyle Verreynne gets low and tries to sweep it away but misses. The ball sneaks under his blade and hits him on the pads. Mehidy Hasan appeals and the umpire raises his dreaded finger. Kyle Verreynne takes the review straightaway. The UltraEdge shows no bat is involved. The Ball Tracking shows that the ball is missing the wickets. The umpire is forced to overturn his original decision. Kyle Verreynne survives. This is the eighth decision that has been overturned in this Test match so far.
Flatter, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to the leg side.
Loopy ball, around off, it turns in sharply. Kyle Verreynne goes back and tucks it to short leg.
Back of a length, outside off. It nips away a long way. Ryan Rickelton looks to chase it but misses.
A full-length ball, on the fifth stump. Ryan Rickelton taps it to the off side.
Full length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it out watchfully.
Full length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton punches it to deep point for one.
Length ball, on the pads. Kyle Verreynne flicks it to square leg for a single.
Just two runs off the over then! Full length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton defends it on the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mehidy Hasan strikes again in the afternoon session. Exceptional effort in the field by Shadman Islam. It is floated, full and on off. Kyle Verreynne tries to reverse-sweep it. He does not middle it though. The ball takes the under-edge, lands on his boot and lobs to the left of silly point. Shadman Islam shows good presence of mind here, as he was up in the air trying to evade the reverse-hit. He later realises that the ball is in the air to his left. He then stretches out his left and takes a stunning catch.
Howout: c Shadman Islam b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: DROPPED! Wiaan Mulder does not depart on a golden duck in this innings. Touch short, outside off. Wiaan Mulder tries to cut it away. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards the man at first slip. He fails to grab the ball and it goes past him. The batters take a single.
On off, blocked out.
Full, on leg, tucked to short leg.
Floated, full and on leg. Ryan Rickelton pushes it out.
On the stumps. Ryan Rickelton goes back and blocks it out.

OH DEAR! Khaled Ahmed drops an easy chance and he is down on the deck. A length ball, around off. Wiaan Mulder tries to flick it away. The ball lobs to the left of the bowler off the leading edge. Khaled Ahmed moves to that side but is unable to grab it cleanly.
Full, on leg. Mulder clips it to mid-wicket.
A short ball, angled down leg. Wiaan Mulder fails to flick it away.
Length, on off. Mulder defends it to mid on.
Good length, outside off. Mulder shoulders his arms at it.
Length ball, on off. Wiaan Mulder defends it out.
Outside off, left alone by Ryan Rickelton.
Floated, around off. It grips and turns away sharply. Ryan Rickelton tries to defend it out but misses.
On off, defended out solidly.
Full, on off. Ryan Rickelton pats it back to the bowler.
Outside off and turning away. Ryan Rickelton leaves it alone for the keeper.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton blocks it to short leg.
A length ball, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
On a length, just outside off. Wiaan Mulder covers his off pole and taps it towards the slip cordon.
Back of a length, around off. Wiaan Mulder blocks it off the back foot.
A bit full, around middle. Wiaan Mulder leans and pushes it to mid on.
On a length, around off. Wiaan Mulder keeps it out, off the front foot.
Pitches it up, around middle. Wiaan Mulder gets forward to defend. The ball goes off the thick inside edge towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
This is a flatter ball, around off. Mulder tries to block it off the back foot. It takes the outside edge and runs past the slip fielder for a single.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Ryan hangs back and cuts it to the cover fielder.
A quicker ball, full and around off. Ryan Rickelton defends it off the front foot.
Floated, full and on middle. Ryan Rickelton pushes it to mid on.
Shorter in length, quicker, outside off. Ryan Rickelton rocks back and punches it towards cover.
Another ball that is quicker and on off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out watchfully.
Back of a length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder stays back and pushes it towards cover, off the back foot.
Shorter in length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder gets low and punches it towards the cover fielder.
Good-length delivery, outside off. Wiaan Mulder lets it through to the keeper.
On a length, just outside off. Wiaan Mulder defends it to the off side.
Back of a length, well outside off. Wiaan Mulder hangs back and slaps it through the cover region. A single taken!
On a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton blocks it to the off side and collects a single.
This is darted on the pads. Ryan Rickelton tucks it past the short leg fielder for a single.
Tosses it up, around middle and leg. Wiaan Mulder looks to flick but he misses and gets hit on his pad, outside the line.
Mulder comes down the track and works it to mid-wicket.
Darted on the pads. Wiaan Mulder tickles it to short fine leg.
Floated, on a length, turning in from outside off. Wiaan Mulder covers his off pole and blocks it.
Tosses it up, around off. Wiaan Mulder blocks it solidly off the front foot.
Good-length ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton dabs it onto the deck.
This is full and outside off. Ryan Rickelton drives it to the cover fielder who stops it with a dive to his right.
Back of a length, around middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton tucks it around the corner and rotates the strike.
A stifled appeal for LBW but there was certainly some inside edge on it. A full ball, angling in from middle. Wiaan Mulder gets an inside edge onto his pad. The ball rolls to fine leg for a run.
Short of a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton gets on top of the bounce and defends it.
This lands on a good length, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton stays back and taps it to the off side.
Tossed up, around off. Wiaan Mulder gets forward and keeps it out.
Mulder runs down the track and eases this full ball to mid on.
Tossed up delivery, around off. Wiaan Mulder lunges forward and blocks it.
In the air but safe! This is darted on the pads. Wiaan Mulder looks to sweep it fine but he miscues it. The ball probably hit the glove and lobs up behind the leg slip fielder for a single.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Ryan Rickelton lets it be.
Full and around middle. Ryan Rickelton drives it to the mid on fielder. THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4!
Taskin starts with a length ball, around off. Wiaan Mulder prods to block it.
A full ball, outside off. Wiaan Mulder drives it to the cover fielder.
Good-length delivery, around middle. Wiaan Mulder gets solid in his front foot defence.
On a length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder leaves it alone.
Back of a length, outside off. Wiaan Mulder pushes it through the off side and takes a single.
A length ball, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
Tossed up, on middle. Wiaan Mulder blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter ball, on a length, around off. Wiaan Mulder keeps it out, off the back foot.
Hasan changes his angle and comes 'round the wicket. This is around leg. Wiaan Mulder tickles it through fine leg for a brace.
On a length, around leg. Mulder tucks it around the corner and settles for a run.
FOUR BYES! A loopy ball, full and just outside off. Ryan Rickelton looks to reverse-sweep but he misses. The keeper fails to grab the ball and it races away to the fence.
Around off, blocked out.
Good-length ball, around off. Wiaan Mulder blocks it to the off side.

NOT OUT! That was clearly a bump ball! A very full ball, outside off, almost a yorker-length delivery. Mulder looks to dig it out but he misses and the ball sneaks under his bat. Bangladesh appeal for a caught behind but the on-field umpires are not sure. They take it upstairs. The replays roll in and it shows that the ball bounced off the surface before going to the keeper.
Good-length ball, outside off. Wiaan Mulder looks to push it through the off side but it goes off the thick inside edge past the leg stump for a single.
On a length, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
Back of a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton hangs back and defends it to cover.
Fuller in length, on middle. Ryan Rickelton flicks it through the square leg region for a brace.

OUT! CAUGHT! Mehidy Hasan strikes yet again! Lovely delivery from the youngster! Hasan tosses it up nicely, outside off, from 'round the wicket, enticing the batter to drive. Mulder prods and looks to drive it through cover. Although, he only manages a thick outside edge which goes straight to Yasir Ali at first slip who takes a sharp catch. South Africa lose their sixth wicket now!
Howout: c Yasir Ali b Mehidy Hasan

Commentary: Full and outside off. Keshav Maharaj drives but finds the wide mid off fielder.

Nicely done! Another ball, full and outside off. Maharaj gets forward and drives it through the vacant cover region. The batters take three runs. The cover fielder gives it a chase and does well to keep the ball in play.
FOUR! A wayward ball, full and down leg. Ryan Rickelton kneels and sweeps it behind square on the leg side for a boundary.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Ryan Rickelton cuts it past the cover-point fielder for one run.
Uppish but safe! Tossed up, just outside off. Keshav Maharaj skips down the track and just chips it over the mid off fielder for a brace.

FOUR! Ryan Rickelton choosing the aggressive path now. Full length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton leans in and drives it through covers for a boundary. This is as good as it gets for Ryan Rickelton. He seems to have his eye in at the moment.
Excellent batting! Following a boundary with a single. Length ball, angled down leg. Ryan Rickelton clips it to fine leg for a single.
Fuller, on off. Keshav Maharaj drives it to extra cover. The fielder there dives to his right to make a sharp stop.

OUT! LBW! What a delivery! Taskin Ahmed gets his second wicket here. Keshav Maharaj walks back on a timid score. A full-length ball, slanting in from outside off. Keshav Maharaj tries to defend it out on the front foot but misses to get any blade on it. He gets pinged on his pad. Taskin Ahmed appeals and the umpire raises his finger in a flash.
Howout: lbw b Taskin Ahmed

Commentary: Taskin Ahmed fires in a yorker, on off. Simon Harmer digs it out solidly.
Taskin Ahmed goes for another yorker, even this is in the blockhole. Simon Harmer digs it out watchfully. Taskin Ahmed is bowling with fire with an injured shoulder. This is excellent stuff.
Fuller, outside off, turns away with some extra bounce. Ryan Rickelton lets it be.
Full, on middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton clips it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Full, on off, blocked out solidly.
On the stumps, defended back to the bowler.
Fuller, on off. Simon Harmer eases it back to Hasan.
Looped up, around middle and leg. Simon Harmer defends it on the front foot.
Full length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton pushes it to cover.
On a length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton taps it to deep point for a single.
Full length, around off. Simon Harmer works it to third man off the outside edge, The batters take a couple.
Length ball, on leg. Simon Harmer clips it to short mid-wicket.
Full length, on off. Simon Harmer drives it to the left of mid on. The fielder races to his left and makes a great stop.
A length ball, on off. Simon Harmer defends it out watchfully.
Around off, Ryan Rickelton blocks it out.
Tosses it up, on off stump. Ryan Rickelton goes back and defends it to the off side.
Fuller, on off. Ryan Rickelton sweeps it to short fine leg. The keeper gives it a chase. They take one.
Full and down leg. Simon Harmer clips it to square leg.
Floated, full and down leg. Simon Harmer tucks it to the leg side.
Full, on off. Simon Harmer blocks it on the front foot.
Length ball, on the pads. Ryan Rickelton tucks it to mid-wicket.
A length ball, on middle and leg. Ryan Rickelton stays back, clips it to square leg for one.
Full length, outside off. Simon Harmer drives it to cover but straight to the fielder.

BEAUTY! Ebadot Hossain asking the right questions. A length ball, outside off. This one holds its line after hitting the deck. Simon Harmer tries to defend it inside the line but gets beaten on the outside edge.

On a length, around off. Simon Harmer looks to push it away. The ball goes towards the slip cordon off the outside edge. Mahmudul Hasan Joy, at second slip, dives to his left and makes a sharp stop. Saves a certain boundary to be honest.
Length ball, on the pads. Simon Harmer nudges it to mid-wicket for one. The lead moves to 259.
A full ball, on middle. Simon Harmer eases it to long on for a run.
Floated, full and outside off. Ryan Rickelton looks for a reverse-sweep but he misses.
Flatter and on off. Ryan Rickelton rocks back and pushes it to cover for a run.
A loopy ball, outside off. Simon Harmer reverse-sweeps but the ball hits the first slip fielder.
Floated, on a length, around middle. Simon Harmer sits back and tucks it to square leg.
Flatter and quicker, on off. Simon Harmer pushes it back to the bowler.
Good-length delivery, around off. Ryan Rickelton keeps it out.
Fuller in length, outside off. Ryan Rickelton squeezes it out.
A short ball, angling down leg. Ryan Rickelton sways away from the line of the ball.
A full ball, on middle. Ryan Rickelton flicks it to the mid-wicket fielder.
Back of a length, just outside off. Ryan Rickelton dabs it onto the deck.
A full ball, around leg. Ryan Rickelton glances it through fine leg. The fielder in the deep moves to his left, puts in a dive and saves a couple of runs for his side.
Floated, on a length, on leg. Simon Harmer wrists it to short leg.
SIX! BANG! Good use of the feet from Harmer! Tossed up, pn off. Simon Harmer skips down the track and bludgeons it over the deep mid-wicket region for a biggie.
Fuller, on leg. Simon Harmer tucks it to square leg for a quick single.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Ryan Rickelton rocks back and pushes it through the off side for one run. 200 comes up for South Africa!

Is that a run out? A direct hit at the bowler's end and Simon Harmer might be in trouble. Yes, the replays roll in and it shows that Harmer is well short of his crease. This was a flatter ball, outside off. Harmer cuts it through the cover region. He completes the second run with ease and looks to steal the third run. Although, Nurul Hasan (sub) collects the ball from the deep and scores a direct hit at the non-striker's end. South Africa lose their eighth wicket now!
Howout: run out (sub Nurul Hasan)

Commentary: Tossed up, around off. Ryan Rickelton taps it to the off side and takes a single.

OUT! RUN OUT! Oh, dear! South Africa are losing their way here! Cricketing suicide from South Africa! Lizaad Williams looks to steal a run off the misfield but ends up throwing away his wicket. This was a short ball, around middle. Ryan Rickelton pulls it towards square leg for a run. The fielder there hurls a wayward throw towards the keeper. Liton Das fails to grab the ball and Williams looks to take another run. Ryan isn't interested and he sends him back. Shadman Islam at point, throws the ball back to the keeper who whips the bails off. Williams is well short of his crease.
Howout: run out (Shadman Islam / Liton Das)

Commentary: OUT! LBW!
Full length, outside off. Duanne Olivier lets it be.
BEATEN! Full length, outside off. Duanne Olivier tries to push it away. He gets beaten on the outside edge.
Full length, angled into the pads. Duanne Olivier tucks it to short mid-wicket.

OUT! LBW! That is it! Ebadot Hossain gets the last wicket. This was a length ball, jagging back in from outside off. Duanne Olivier looks to block it off the back foot but he misses as the ball sneaks through his bat. Olivier gets hit on his pad and Bangladesh appeal. The umpire agrees but Olivier sends it upstairs. The Ball Tracker rolls in and it indicates three reds. South Africa are bowled out for 204!
Howout: lbw b Ebadot Hossain

Commentary: Tossed up, outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy pushes it back to the bowler.
On a length, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
FOUR! Cut away! Flatter ball, short and outside off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy cuts it through the point region for a boundary. Bangladesh are up and running!
Nicely tossed up, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy blocks it off the front foot.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy dead-bats it.
A quicker ball, going on with the angle from off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drags it back to the bowler.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Shadman Islam digs it out back to the bowler.

OUT! CAUGHT! Exactly the kind of start that South Africa would have hoped for! Shadman Islam departs for a duck! This is tossed up, around off and turning away a tad. Shadman Islam looks to defend off the front foot but it takes the outside edge and goes straight to Keegan Petersen at first slip who takes a simple catch. Bangladesh under pressure straightaway!
Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Simon Harmer

Commentary: Around off. Blocked out.
Full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drills it to long off for a single.
Floated, full and around off. Mahmudul Hasan Joy keeps it out.
This is a flatter ball, full and on middle. Mahmudul Hasan Joy drags it back to the bowler. End of a successful over for South Africa!
Flatter ball, around leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto tickles it behind square on the leg side. Not in the gap though!
Outside off. Blocked out.
Flatter and on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets solid in his front foot defence.
Slightly short and spinning in from outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it off the back foot.
Flatter and on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it out.
Around leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto nudges it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Floated, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it off the front foot.
An appeal for caught behind but the umpire says no! Flatter and quicker, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto stays back to cut but he misses.
Nicely tossed up, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto keeps it out.
Around off, defended.
A flatter ball, going on with the arm, from middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto stays back and tucks it to mid-wicket.
Full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto pushes it back to the bowler. A maiden over from Simon Harmer!

OUT! TIMBER! Keshav Maharaj strikes now and this is a huge wicket for South Africa, as the centurion of the first innings goes for a timid score in the second. Keshav Maharaj takes off for a celebratory run! Excellent bowling from Maharaj! This was tossed up, on a length and went on with the angle from middle. Joy prods to block but the ball sneaks through his bat. It hits the pad and ricochets onto the leg stump. Bangladesh are in deep trouble now.
Howout: b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Tossed up, on middle. Blocked out.
Flatter and full and on middle. Mominul Haque tucks it to mid-wicket.
Edged but safe! Floated, full and around off. Mominul Haque prods to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the slip fielder. The batters take two runs.

OUT! LBW! Another one bites the dust and this time it is Bangladesh's skipper who has to walk back to the hut. South Africa are all over Bangladesh at the moment! This is a flatter ball, on a length and turning in from outside off. Mominul Haque rocks back and looks to work it on the leg side. He misses and gets pinged on his pad. South Africa appeal and the umpire raises his finger in no time. Mominul Haque has a chat with his partner but doesn't take the review. Bangladesh slip further!
Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: A dot to end the over! After a quiet first innings, Keshav Maharaj makes a solid statement in the second innings by taking two wickets in three overs. It is full and outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim defends it to the off side.
Flighted, full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto prods and blocks it back to the bowler.
Fuller, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto dabs it to point.
Flatter and quicker, on the pads. Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it through mid-wicket for a brace.
Looped up, full and on the stumps. Najmul Hossain Shanto prods and defends it to the leg side off the inner half.
Around off, defended out watchfully.
Touch short, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it to the left of mid on for a single.
A full ball, on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it to long on and takes a single. Bangladesh are underway on Day 5!
Flatter and quicker, around off. Mushfiqur Rahim stays back and dabs it onto the deck.
That stayed a tad low! Floated, on a length, around off. Rahim hangs back and manages to keep it out.
Flatter and quicker, outside off. Mushfiqur Rahim stays back and punches it to the cover fielder.

OUT! Mushfiqur Rahim has been adjudged LBW but he has sent it upstairs. Huge moment in this game. The UltraEdge rolls in and it confirms that there was no bat involved. The Ball Tracker indicates three reds and Rahim is a goner! This is exactly the kind of start that the Proteas would have wished for! They get rid of the experienced Mushfiqur Rahim in the very first over and Keshav Maharaj is over the moon. This was a flatter ball, landing around middle and going on with the arm. Rahim prods and looks to block. He misses and gets rapped in front. He played for the turn there but there wasn't any of it. Bangladesh on the backfoot straightaway.
Howout: lbw b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Floated, on a length, outside off. Liton Das stays back and taps it to point.
Loopy ball, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it back to the bowler.
Full length, wide outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto steers it through backward point for a brace.
Floated, full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it to mid off.
Looped up, full and on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto defends it on the front foot.
Tossed up, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it back to Harmer.
Loopy ball, full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto prods and blocks it out safely.
On a length, around off. Liton Das keeps it out.
Tossed up nicely, around off. Liton Das gets forward and defends it.
Slower through the air, on a length, around off. Liton Das dead-bats it.
Nicely worked to the leg side! Flatter ball, shorter in length, on middle. Das rocks back and whips it in front of square on the leg side for a brace.

OUT! CAUGHT! A soft dismissal and Keshav Maharaj is on a roll at Kingsmead! Two wickets in two overs for Keshav Maharaj on Day 5! He bags his fourth wicket of the innings and the Proteas are bossing this Test now. This was tossed up, on middle. Das plants his front foot forward and looks to play it across the line. It goes off the leading edge straight to Simon Harmer at mid on who takes a dolly. Bangladesh lose their fifth wicket and they are in deep, deep trouble.
Howout: c Simon Harmer b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Floated, full and around off. Yasir Ali keeps it out, off the front foot.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it wide of the mid off fielder and takes a single.
This one turns in late from middle. Ali hangs back and tickles it towards short fine leg for a run. Ali is off the mark!
Floated, full and on middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets forward and works it to short leg.
Nice and full, looped up, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets to the pitch of the ball and blocks it.

FOUR! Good use of the feet from Shanto! Bangladesh many more of these! Flighted delivery, on a length, around middle. Shanto shimmies down the track and lofts it over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Tosses it up, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto leans and mistimes his drive towards the cover fielder.
Fuller, on off. Yasir Ali blocks it out solidly.
FOUR! Nicely played. Yasir Ali taking the aggressive route. It is short, outside off. Yasir Ali stays back and slaps it through covers for a boundary.
Around off, blocked back to the bowler.
Full and on the stumps. Yasir Ali blocks it out to mid off.

OUT! TIMBER! Keshav Maharaj, YOU BEAUTY! He picks up a five-fer here, in no time. This is a stunning delivery to get rid of Ali. It drifts in, around middle. The ball grips and turns away off the deck. Yasir Ali tries to defend it off the front foot, but misses it completely. The ball zips past the outside edge and uproots the off stump. Keshav Maharaj with yet another victory lap in this Test match. Bangladesh slip further.
Howout: b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Full, on the stumps, blocked out solidly.

SIX! BOOM! Najmul Hossain Shanto trying to put up a fight here. But he needs more of these results. Fuller, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets under it and smokes it over the long off fence for a biggie.
No run.Floated and full, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto gently pushes it back to Harmer.
Tosses up, on off. Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it to mid-wicket for a quick single.
Full, on middle and leg. Mehidy Hasan tucks it to short leg.
Fuller, outside off. Mehidy Hasan tries to drive it on the front foot. But ends up working it back to the bowler off the inner half.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time Simon Harmer has his say on Day 5! It is full and outside off. Mehidy Hasan prods and tries to defend it out but misses. The ball takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. Keegan Petersen there, gets low to his left and takes a sharp catch. Simon Harmer is ecstatic, as he punches the air. What a performance this has been by Simon Harmer after coming back into the side.
Howout: c Keegan Petersen b Simon Harmer

Commentary: Fuller, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto works it to long on for a single.
Full, on off. Taskin Ahmed flicks it to mid-wicket for a single.
Flighted, full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto reaches out and pushes it back to the bowler.
Full and outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto taps it back to the bowler.
Quicker, full, around middle and leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto goes back, tucks it to mid-wicket for one.
Swing and a miss! Tossed up, outside off. Taskin Ahmed tries to chase it but misses. He gets beaten on the outside edge.
Loopy ball, around off, drifting in. Najmul Hossain Shanto leans forward and tries to defend it. The ball though grips and turns away sharply. It zips past the outside edge.
Fuller, on leg. Shanto fails to block it out. He gets pinged on his pads. Going down leg.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto blocks it to short leg.
Fuller, around off. Shanto drives it off the inner half back to the bowler.
On off, defended out solidly.
Tossed up, around middle. Najmul Hossain Shanto prods and blocks it to short leg.
SIX! BANG! Taskin Ahmed freeing his arms now. It is floated, full and around off. Taskin Ahmed prods and slogs it over the mid-wicket fence for a maximum.
Full, outside off. Ahmed drives it to cover for a single.
Fuller, on the pads, this one stays a bit low. Najmul Hossain Shanto goes back and clips it to deep square leg for three runs.
Fuller, outside off. Taskin Ahmed drives it through covers for three runs. Maharaj is enticing both the left-handed batters to play away from their body.
Floated, full and on leg. Najmul Hossain Shanto flicks it to the leg side for an easy single.
Fuller, on middle and leg. Taskin Ahmed blocks it out watchfully towards mid on.
Floated, around off. Najmul Hossain Shanto keeps it out.
Nicely tossed up, outside off and spinning away late. Najmul Hossain Shanto prods and lets it be.
An overpitched ball, outside off. Najmul Hossain Shanto drives it to the mid off fielder.
This is darted on the pads. Najmul Hossain Shanto rocks back and tucks it wide of the square leg fielder for a brace.

OUT! STUMPED! Another one bites the dust! This has been a terrific morning for South Africa! The spin-twins are doing the job for the Proteas and Bangladesh are on the brink of a Test match defeat! This was tossed up, around off and spinning away from the batter. Najmul Hossain Shanto gets forward to defend but he misses as the ball zips past his outside edge. Shanto also loses his balance in the process. Kyle Verreynne behind the sticks, collects the ball cleanly and whips the bails off. Shanto has no part of his back foot inside the crease and Bangladesh lose their eighth wicket.
Howout: st Kyle Verreynne b Simon Harmer

Commentary: Around off. Blocked out.
Nicely tossed up, around off. Taskin Ahmed keeps it out watchfully.

An appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved! South Africa have sent it upstairs. Wickets missing on the Ball Tracker and Taskin Ahmed survives! This was floated, around middle and turning in late. Taskin Ahmed looks to defend but he misses and gets hit on his pad. South Africa appeal and opt for a review as the umpire says no. The Ball Tracker suggests that the ball would have spun way down leg.
Tossed up, around middle. Taskin Ahmed blocks it.
Tossed up, outside off. Taskin Ahmed kneels and looks to slog-sweep but he miscues it high in the air towards the deep square leg region for a run.

OUT! TAKEN! This it turning out to be an extraordinary morning for South Africa! A horrow show for Bangladesh though! Maharaj bowls it slower and wider of off. Khaled Ahmed gets down on his knee and looks to heave it over the deep mid-wicket fence. He only manages a top edge though which goes high in the air towards the mid-wicket region. Lizaad Williams runs forward from mid on, settles under it and takes a good catch. South Africa are just 1 wicket away from going 1-0 up in the series.
Howout: c Lizaad Williams b Keshav Maharaj

Commentary: Tossed up, around middle. Taskin Ahmed keeps it out watchfully.
A loopy ball, around off. Ebadot Hossain gets forward and blocks it to the off side.
A bit flatter, full and outside off. Ebadot Hossain stretches forward and defends it to point.
Flatter and quicker, around off. Hossain rocks back and dabs it onto the deck.
On a length, turning in from outside off. Ebadot Hossain covers his off pole and dead-bats it.
Floated, full and around off. Hossain gets solid in his front foot defence.
Tosses it up, on off. Ebadot Hossain defends it solidly yet again. A maiden over from Simon Harmer!
Full and outside off. Taskin Ahmed drives it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery, outside off. Taskin Ahmed gets forward and defends it.
This is an overpitched ball, outside off. Taskin Ahmed drives it through cover and takes a couple of runs.
Around middle. Blocked out.
Tossed up, on middle and leg. Taskin Ahmed defends it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! There it is! Keshav Maharaj gets his seventh wicket and ends Bangladesh's misery! What a performance this has been from Keshav Maharaj on his home ground! This time he comes 'round the wicket and serves a flatter ball, on a length, going on with the arm from middle. Taskin Ahmed stays back to block but the ball takes the outside edge of the bat and goes straight to Wiaan Mulder at first slip who takes a sitter. Bangladesh are bundled out for 53. South Africa win by 220 runs!
Howout: c Wiaan Mulder b Keshav Maharaj
